---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Apps — Mapache Softworks GmbH"
	description="Renamer and Archiver are independent productivity apps published by Mapache Softworks GmbH."
>
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container">
			<p class="eyebrow">Products</p>
			<h1>Independent tools for everyday file work.</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				The current product line focuses on utility software that helps people work faster without hiding important choices from them.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<div class="container grid two">
			<article class="card">
				<p class="eyebrow">Renamer 7</p>
				<h2>Batch File Renamer</h2>
				<p>Rename thousands of files at once with reusable workflows, live previews, smart undo, and support for common photo, music, extension, CSV, and regular-expression tasks.</p>
				<ul class="tag-list">
					<li>macOS 15+</li>
					<li>Windows 10+</li>
					<li>Local AI Assist</li>
				</ul>
				<div class="card-actions">
					<a class="button" href="https://renamer.com/mac">Open Renamer</a>
					<a class="button-secondary" href="https://renamer.com/download/mac">Download for Mac</a>
				</div>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<p class="eyebrow">Archiver 5</p>
				<h2>Archive Utility for macOS</h2>
				<p>Open RAR, Zip, 7zip, and dozens more formats. Preview archives before extracting, create password-protected archives, split large files, and handle multiple archives in parallel.</p>
				<ul class="tag-list">
					<li>macOS 26+</li>
					<li>Archive preview</li>
					<li>Encrypted archives</li>
				</ul>
				<div class="card-actions">
					<a class="button" href="https://archiverapp.com">Open Archiver</a>
					<a class="button-secondary" href="https://incrediblebee.com/download/archiver-5">Download</a>
				</div>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<div class="container panel">
			<p class="eyebrow">Possible next sections</p>
			<h2>Where this page can go next.</h2>
			<ul class="list">
				<li><strong>Support hub:</strong> downloads, purchase recovery, app support, and contact links.</li>
				<li><strong>Release notes:</strong> a lightweight changelog for each app.</li>
				<li><strong>Product detail pages:</strong> screenshots, feature tours, FAQs, and platform-specific notes.</li>
				<li><strong>Trust pages:</strong> privacy, local processing, licensing, and data handling for app features such as AI Assist.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
